summary: This is a travel authorization email from the DOJ's E2 travel system approving a trip to Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-7, 2020 for the purpose of conducting witness interviews related to the Epstein investigation (case reference 2018R01618). The authorization is pending further approval.

events.title: Planned Witness Interviews in Stockholm
events.description: DOJ personnel travel to Stockholm, Sweden to conduct witness interviews for the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The DOJ was actively conducting witness interviews for the Epstein investigation as of early 2020.
Travel was authorized to Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-7, 2020 for these interviews.
The investigation had a case reference number: 2018R01618 and a trip purpose code: R20NYS13342.
The travel authorization was processed through the DOJ's E2 travel system and was pending further approval at the time of the email.
